      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LOTS OF CHANGE (3) was once again right in the mix last start when runner-up over 2185m at this track, beaten 4.5 metres. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Meets a comparable field and he can go right on with the job. GRAND MAJESTIC BELLS NZ (7) ran fifth last start at Gloucester Park over 2130m, beaten 18 metres. Expect her to pose a serious challenge. MAJESTIC LINE (10) was out of the money two runs ago then broke following some interference but still managed to finish third, beaten 4.5 metres, over 2116m at this track a week ago. Hard to know where she gets from this slightly awkward draw. Only needs to get things right to be in the money again. ELISH STAR (1) is next best and gets every chance from a favourable draw.",
